article.description: — Al-Amir Dawes' 25 points helped Seton Hall defeat Northeastern 88-75 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Dawes puts up 25 as Seton Hall defeats Northeastern 88-75
article.linkText: Dawes puts up 25 as Seton Hall defeats Northeastern 88-75
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- — Al-Amir Dawes' 25 points helped Seton Hall defeat Northeastern 88-75 on Wednesday night. Dawes also contributed five rebounds and five assists for the Pirates (5-2). Kadary Richmond added 21 points while shooting 9 of 16 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line, and he also had six rebounds and six assists. Jaden Bediako shot 4 of 4 from the field and 5 for 6 from the line to finish with 13 points. Jared Turner led the way for the Huskies (3-5) with 18 points. Harold Woods added 11 points and eight rebounds for Northeastern. Luka Sakota also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
